DispatcherPriorityAwaitable Struct

Definition

Represents an awaitable object that asynchronously yields control back to the current dispatcher and provides an opportunity for the dispatcher to process other events

In this Article

public struct DispatcherPriorityAwaitable
Inheritance
Object
System.ValueType
DispatcherPriorityAwaitable

Remarks

The Yield method returns a DispatcherPriorityAwaitable.

Methods

GetAwaiter()

Returns an object that waits for the completion of an asynchronous task.

public System.Windows.Threading.DispatcherPriorityAwaiter GetAwaiter ();
Returns
DispatcherPriorityAwaiter

An object that waits for the completion of an asynchronous task.
